From: Chao Zeng <chao.zeng@siemens.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:47:35 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 03/17] Workaround to correct DP clock to 154MHZ

BUG: as the default DPI source should be DPI_1_IN_CLK
     but seems the DSS input clk swap the DPI0 and DPI1
     so change the DPI clock to DPI0 to provide the clock
     to DPI

Signed-off-by: Chao Zeng <chao.zeng@siemens.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-pg2.dtsi | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-pg2.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-pg2.dtsi
index ca20f2d9dec6..63bf5a805aeb 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-pg2.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-pg2.dtsi
@@ -770,7 +770,7 @@ &dss {
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
 	pinctrl-0 = <&dss_vout1_pins_default>;
 
-	assigned-clocks = <&k3_clks 67 2>;
+	assigned-clocks = <&k3_clks 67 0>;
 	assigned-clock-parents = <&k3_clks 67 5>;
 };
 
